3 On page 2, delete lines 3 through 45 and on page 3, delete lines 1 through
4 41 and insert:
5 “SECTION 2. ORS 456.508 is amended to read:
6 “456.508. As used in ORS 456.510 and 456.513:
7 “(1) ‘Accessible’ means that housing complies with federal accessibility
8 guidelines implementing the Fair Housing Amendments Act of 1988, 42 U.S.C.
9 3601 et seq., as amended and in effect on [January 1, 2004] the effective date
10 of this 2026 Act, or section 504 of the Rehabilitation Act of 1973 (29
11 U.S.C. 794), as amended and in effect on the effective date of this 2026
12 Act and as specified under 24 C.F.R. part 8, subpart C.
13 “(2) ‘Common living space’ means a living room, family room, dining room
14 or kitchen.
15 “(3) ‘Contiguous units’ means units that are on the same tax lot or on
16 contiguous tax lots that have a common boundary[.], including tax lots that
17 are separated by a public road [are contiguous tax lots for purposes of this
18 subsection].
19 “(4)(a) ‘New’ means that the housing being constructed did not previously
20 exist in residential or nonresidential form.
21 “(b) ‘New’ does not include the acquisition, alteration, renovation or re-

1 modeling of an existing structure.
2 “(5) ‘Powder room’ means a room containing at least a toilet and sink.
3 “(6) ‘Rental housing’ means a dwelling unit designed for nonowner occu-
4 pancy under a tenancy typically lasting six months or longer.
5 “(7) ‘Subsidized development’ means housing that receives one or more of
6 the following development subsidies from the Housing and Community Ser-
7 vices Department:
8 “(a) The federal low-income housing tax credit under 26 U.S.C. 42(a), if
9 no part of the eligible basis prior to the application of 26 U.S.C. 42(i)(2)(B)
10 was financed with an obligation described in 26 U.S.C. 42(h)(4)(A), all as
11 amended and in effect on [January 1, 2004] the effective date of this 2026
12 Act;
13 “(b) An agriculture workforce housing tax credit, as described in ORS
14 315.164;
15 “(c) A loan that qualifies the lending institution for a subsidized housing
16 loan tax credit, as described in ORS 317.097;
17 “(d) Funding under the federal HOME Investment Partnerships Act, 42
18 U.S.C. 12721 to 12839, as amended and in effect on [January 1, 2004] the ef-
19 fective date of this 2026 Act;
20 “(e) Moneys from the Oregon Housing Fund created under ORS 458.620;
21 or
22 “(f) Moneys from other grant or tax incentive programs administered by
23 the Housing and Community Services Department under ORS 456.559.
24 “(8) ‘Visitable’ means capable of being approached, entered and used by
25 individuals with mobility impairments, including but not limited to individ-
26 uals using wheelchairs.
27 “SECTION 3. ORS 456.510 is amended to read:
28 “456.510. (1) Except as provided in this section and ORS 456.513, the
29 Housing and Community Services Department may not provide funding for
30 the development of new rental housing that is a subsidized development un-
SB 1576-1 2/2/26
Proposed Amendments to SB 1576 Page 2

1 less:
2 “(a) Each dwelling unit of the housing meets the following requirements:
3 “(A) At least one visitable exterior route leading to a dwelling unit en-
4 trance that is stepless and has a minimum clearance of 32 inches.
5 “(B) One or more visitable routes between the visitable dwelling unit
6 entrance and a visitable common living space.
7 “(C) At least one visitable common living space.
8 “(D) One or more visitable routes between the dwelling unit entrance and
9 a powder room.
10 “(E) A powder room doorway that is stepless and has a minimum clear-
11 ance of 32 inches.
12 “(F) A powder room with walls that are reinforced in a manner suitable
13 for handrail installation.
14 “(G) Light switches, electrical outlets and environmental controls that
15 are at a reachable height.
16 “(b) For a development that has a shared community room or that has 20
17 or more contiguous units, there is at least one powder room available for all
18 tenants and guests that is accessible.
19 “(c) The subsidized development complies with the accessibility
20 standards under section 504 of the Rehabilitation Act of 1973 (29 U.S.C.
21 794), as amended and in effect on the effective date of this 2026 Act
22 and as specified under 24 C.F.R. part 8, subpart C.
23 “(2) For a multistory structure without an elevator, this section applies
24 only to dwelling units on the ground floor of the structure.
25 “(3) This section does not apply to agriculture workforce housing as de-
26 fined in ORS 315.163 that is located on a farm.
27 “SECTION 4. (1) The amendments to ORS 447.220, 456.508 and 456.510
28 by sections 1 to 3 of this 2026 Act become operative on January 1, 2027.
29 “(2) The Director of the Department of Consumer and Business
30 Services and the Housing and Community Services Department may
